Creating Top two Slicers State and Port Name 12

Creating state  Slicer 

- Bring slicer from the visualization to the report pane 

- Select state from the fields 

-Select slicer and change drop down from the down aero 

 - Format 

           Outline color = , Outline Weight = 6, X position = 795, Y position = 0 , Width = 195, Height = 106

            ( Place the slicer next to the Title Text Box)

            Slicer Heading = on > Font Color=, Background = , Text Size = 11, Font Family = Segoe ( Bold)

            Items > Item Color= . Background= , Text Size = 9, Font Family = Arial Black 

          Title = Off 

         Background = Off

         Lock space   = Off

         Border     =  Off 

        Shadow      = Off

      Visual Heading = On 

Creating  Port Name   Slicer 

- Bring slicer from the visualization to the report pane 

- Select Port Name  from the fields 

-Select slicer and change drop down from the down aero 

 - Format 

           Outline color = , Outline Weight = 6, X position = 992, Y position = 0 , Width = 195, Height = 106

            ( Place the slicer next to the State Slicer )

            Slicer Heading = on > Font Color=, Background = , Text Size = 11, Font Family = Segoe ( Bold)

            Items > Item Color= . Background= , Text Size = 9, Font Family = Arial Black 

          Title = Off 

         Background = Off

         Lock space   = Off

         Border     =  Off 

        Shadow      = Off

      Visual Heading = On 


 

How to create a slicer ?  Watch 

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SA43PwWCilQ
